  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate, in a primary care setting, the effectiveness of a brief
      self-management behavioral treatment in patients with medically unexplained chronic fatigue.
      The hypothesis will be tested that fatigue self-management will yield improvements in
      fatigue,functioning, and distress in comparison to the two control conditions: standard
      medical care alone or standard medical care plus an attention control symptom monitoring
      condition.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
